  "body": "VC should failover when the EL connected to a BN is offline\r\n\r\n**Background** \r\n\r\nQuestion from user on Discord (obfuscate):\r\n\r\n`Hi there, I am currently experimenting with fail over scenarios in my system. I have the Teku Beacon Node and Validator clients split out into separate processes. I have a primary BN connected to Besu and a secondary BN connected to Nethermind. I have configured the two BN endpoints in the VCs to examine the fail over behaviour. When I bring the primart BN down it fails over to the secondary BN almost instantly which is great! However, when I bring my primary EL client (Besu) down, the VC doesn't seem to failing over the secondary BN (with the healthy Nethermind node connected it).`\r\n\r\nhttps://discord.com/channels/697535391594446898/697539289042649190/1058317129805484082",
